title: Great atmosphere
text: We were greeted at the door, asked if we wanted to do tastings or a paddle, then shown to our table.We ordered paddles at the bar and they were delivered with an explanation of each gin. We also ordered a cheese platter. The music was great - 80s. The place was nice and warm on a wet day, overall a great atmosphere. We will come again.

title: Yummy food & great service.
text: This mexican bar and grill had wonderfully yummy food at reasonable prices. Our waiter gave the best service, he was friendly and very helpful explaining the drinks & food menus. I'd highly recommend this as a great spot to stop for lunch, drinks or afternoon nibbles.

title: Lovely fresh vegan food and great variety.
text: The food was fresh, vegan and plenty to choose from on the menu. Indoor or outdoor seating available. Reasonable priced.

title: Good food, Good service, Good price
text: the food was fresh, tasty and well presented. The service was good & staff were very helpful. We ordered 3 entrees, 4 mains, deserts, and coffee for 8 people, it cost us $29.00 each. The decor isn't flash but the food & service made up for it.

title: Food - works of art.
text: Beautifully present food, good quality, lovely and fresh. Service good. Reasonable priced. Plenty of tables, some outside. Next to Rosanna train station.

title: Beautiful Food, service
text: Lovely, fresh Thai inspired food. Reasonable priced. Friendly helpful staff. Popular so i would recommend booking a table.

title: Creamy Yoghurt
text: Lovely creamy yoghurt with plenty of choice for toppings. I had the honey & walnut and my daughter had the strawberries. Sat outside at enjoyed our yoghurt while watching the world go by.

title: Highly educational
text: If I could only visit one attraction in Athens to learn about life inhe Ancient times this is the place I would choose. Strolling the gardens and getting the idea how the city was laid out is very interesting.

title: Lovely location, poor service
text: The cafe was lovely, set in a ideal location. We were seated indoors in a warehouse feel cafe and after we wandered the grounds. This is a dog friendly place. It will be great when the steakhouse, dairy, brewery & hotel are added. We had the afternoon tea for two. The food was good but it was very slow coming from the kitchen. I'd already finished my pot of tea before it arrived. I asked the waitress to explain what the savour items were as my daughter is pollo vegetarian.(Does not eat red meat) The waitress said she would go find out. She forgot and I had to ask again. She came back & said the meat was pork. So my daughter could only eat 3 out of 5 items. The sweets were nice & we received 8 scones. The jam & cream were runny so we had to asked for spoons to help spread them on our scones, as there were only knifes & forks on the table. We also had to ask for more cream. My husband had the smoked pork belly and said the fat wasn't completely rendered. Plus its was a bit expensive for what he got on his plate. Would love to come back once the service is improved. Overall a disappointing birthday afternoon tea.

title: Great location
text: This Hotel was in a great location because it was in walking distance to all the attractions. The room was clean but not flash. The breakfast buffet was good plenty of choices. The views from the roof top pool & restaurant was great. Prices at the bar were a little on the expensive side but this is what I've come to expect in Hotels. Plenty of nice seating on the roof top.

title: Great views from the top
text: When buying a tickets buy the multi pass as it gets you into all the other historical sites - all within walking distance of each other. Especially liked the Ancient Agora.

title: Awesome Fountains
text: These fountains play every half hour from 7pm to 11pm - the music, lights and fountain dancing display is different every half hour. Some of the water cannons can shoot up to 500ft in the air. It sounds like fireworks going off. You can view the display from any where around the lake.

title: Excellent Mall
text: All the shops you could ever want. Lots of high end shopping. No real bargain stores. Lovely and clean and spacious. Plenty of good places to eat. Check-out the fountains and ceiling displays. Plus you can also view the aquarium from inside the mall.
placeLocation: Emirate of Dubai, United Arab Emirates

title: Luxury Hotel
text: The staff are so friendly & helpful from the moment you arrive. The room was large and luxurious over looking the lake with the Dubai Fountains. The quality of the amenities were of a very high standard. I loved the pillows in the large, comfy bed. As a big tea drink I was happy to see they had TWG tea bags. The chocolates they delivered to my room was a nice surprise.

title: Very informative tour
text: Unfortunately the weather let us down. They provide a poncho which was great but you will need a raincoat or umbrella from the station to the garage to pick up the bike. Our tour guide martina was very informative and helpful. Highly recommend her. Unfortunately 3 bikes ended up getting flat tyres which put a dampener on the day. Because it was raining we missed out on a picnic but we were able to have lunch in a restaurant near the lake which was great.
place: Versailles Bike Tour with Skip-the-Line Entrance to Palace

title: Wonderful food
text: The food came quickly and was cooked to perfection. Everything was fresh and tasty. We had the all you can eat for $32.90 and we left full. just order a few doses at a time until you are full. Very busy. Chose from 2 seatings - 5 to 7:30 or 7:30 to 10pm.

title: Lovely building & yummy food
text: The food was good and serving sizes were good too. Reasonable prices. Good selection on menu. Large drinks menu. But very noisy, found it hard to hear my dinner guests. Service was good.

title: Great Motel in Blairgowrie
text: Good location to all attractions on the Mornington Peninsula. Big clean, comfy rooms with modern decor. Large bathrooms,and compact kitchenettes. Second story balcony rooms offer more privacy. Short walk to the beach or shops for breakfast etc.

title: Very busy, must be good.
text: Quick service for a very busy cafe. Great selection on the menu for breakfast. Nothing was too much trouble for the staff. Food was good. Eat inside or outside.

title: Nice pizza.
text: Our duck pizza was very nice and reasonably priced. No one was eating in the restaurant so we took our pizza back to the motel. Decor was very old, dark and tired looking.

title: Lovely location in rustic barn
text: Tucked in off the road among the trees you see a lovely barn where the beer is made. The was a good selection of beers to try plus other drink available for non-beer drinkers. We ordered food which was very tasty but on the small size for the price paid. Plenty of staff on to serve customers.

title: Good, easy stroll with great views.
text: Easy stroll to the broad walk from the lighthouse car park.. But very windy on the broad walk, hold onto your hat. Lots of steps, not suitable for prams. Great views of the coast lines and rough surf. Not suitable for swimming as it too rough.

title: Lovely sunny location on the balcony
text: We had lunch here on a public holiday, the food and service were good. Lots of beer & wine to choose from. The menu was good but not if you are a vegetarian. You can eat in the restaurant or enjoy snacks in the bar. Not really suitable for small children.

title: Great for visitors to Melborne
text: I always take visitors to Melbourne on the City Circle Tram. You can hop on and off anytime. It gives a running commentary of Melbourne's history and its significant buildings.

title: Fabulous views
text: Great 360 degree views of Melbourne. Quick ride up in the lift. If you are adventurous do Skydeck which is a room that protrudes from the building with a glass floor. The room is frosted when you get in and when it is extended from the building everything goes clear when a cracking sound.

title: Lots of fun
text: We did the sunrise tour, so it was a very early start. The bus driver was very professional and extremely well organised. Our bike leader was running late and we had to wait for him to arrive.We were given warm jackets and pants to wear on the summit as the wind chill factor was freezing. Sunrise can get very busy @ Haleakala. Once we were outside the park at 6500ft we were issued our bikes and helmets. The bike leader was great in instructing nervous riders and the bus driver protected us from other vehicles from behind. We let other vehicles pass when it was safe to do so. We stopped at Makawao where we were free to get our lunch and then it was back on our bikes down to the beach. A very easy ride. Loved it!

title: Great snorkelling
text: Once we were checked in and on board we were given a light breakfast. Then it was a calm trip out to Molokini for snorkelling. The staff really look after us making sure we had all our gear and were safe in the water. The water is deep and there is no place to stand on the bottom. Did see lots of fish and I was lucky enough to see an octopus. Then back on board for lunch. Hamburgers and salad.Unfortunately because of all the rain we could not go to see the turtles because of the cloudy water. So it was another snorkel at Molokini. We were lucky enough to see whales on the way back to harbour. There was 3 male whales showing off for a female so we saw an impressive display of breaching and tail slapping. Awesome!

title: Lovely scenery
text: Early 6:45 pick up. Taken for a nice breakfast at a golf course. Great croissants. Then it was a long day on winding, narrow roads with lots of stops for pictures. Lunch was provided. No opportunity for swimming. We stopped at a national park for a 30 min bush walk, where we saw waterfalls and the waves crashing on the coast. Our bus driver was great with lots of local knowledge. We found him very interesting.

title: Great location & views
text: Great location for a tired hotel. Could do with some renovations. Rooms were comfy and clean and the staff were friendly and helpful. Fabulous hula dancing & music in the terrace bar. Next to the beach and broad walk which leads to the shops and restaurants at whalers village.

title: Great food & music
text: The food was very good and reasonable prices. Great service. Formal or casual dining available. Music & singing playing in the afternoon very pleasant. Next to the beach & broadwalk.

title: Great location for sunset
text: Service & Food were not very good. Had better food at other places in Ka'anapali. The prices high for what was served. My husbands drink was spilt because of a wobbly table and another patron had to suggest to staff they should replace it. I had to request water and we had to find someone when we left so we could pay the bill.

title: Very busy Restaurant
text: Loud and busy and had to wait 40 minutes for a table. Food was nice. Service was good. Had to go looking for our waiter when leaving so we could pay the bill.

title: Yummy Hot Chocolates
text: Went there for afternoon tea and they had a promotion - 31 different hot chocolate flavours for the month of August. I had an amazing snickers hot chocolate and my girlfriend had the lemon cheese cake hot chocolate. Both were yummy!

title: Great place for lunch
text: We had lunch in the cafe and everything was lovely and fresh. You can get tea & coffee refills. Nice garden out back by the creek. Try the besting.

title: Australian animals galore
text: This is the best place to take oversea visitors so they can see all the animals in Australia. Allow at least 2 hours for a leisurely stroll around the grounds. The birds of the sky is a must see at 12 or 2:30pm

title: Lovely food
text: The food was lovely and fresh. They had a great menu to choose from for breakfast and lunch. There was indoor and outdoor seating available.

title: Great view & Food
text: Beautiful view over looking the vines on a hot or cold day. The service was exceptional, we had the most helpful waiter. The food was very nice but a bit on the expensive side for what it was.

title: So relaxing.
text: Beautiful location among the brush on a hill side, very tranquil and relaxing. The hot pools are different temperatures so you are bound to find one that suits. The dreaming day spa is quiter as no kids are allowed. The bath house is more suitable for families. The massage was heavenly.

title: Beautiful food, service & decor
text: The food was delicious and fresh, the waiters were constantly offering plates from their trays. The decor was modern, warm and clean. The staff were friendly and helpful. The lunch service was quick to cater for the office workers. Great variety of teas to choose from. I would definitely come again.

title: Great place for relaxing
text: This resort is great place to spend a relaxing day by the pool. There is a swim up bar which has great service or you can swim in the ocean. The restaurant serves great food. I recommend the nacho's for two. The staff are fabulous , they kept us supplied with drinks and food. The money you pay on entry is used as credit for your food and drink bill. The double day beds are the best.

title: A wonderful experience
text: No one else was booked in the day I did my class, so I had a private one on one class with the chef. He was really nice and I felt very relaxed and comfortable as he taught me step by step. I had 3 choices of menu's to cook from. The setting was absolutely beautiful in the resort near the pool. At the end of class the 3 courses were beautifully dished up and presented to me for lunch. On leaving I received a certificate and my apron from the day. I was picked up and dropped off from my accommodation.
place: Balinese Cooking Class at The Amala

title: Very Busy
text: This attraction was very busy at 3pm and apparently it gets busier at sunset. It is a short walk from the car park past lots and lots of stall selling tourist souvenirs.

title: First class
text: Lovely setting, beautiful decor, relaxed feel. Plus great food and drinks, with a great view of the beach.

title: Good affordable food
text: Traditional greek restaurant with all the favourites. The owner and chef was a great host, making sure we enjoyed ourselves.

title: Great restaurant
text: You can sit on the stairs for drinks & nibbles or eat in the restaurant upstairs or down stairs. Upstairs has a retractable roof which was fabulous. Beautiful food and great service.

title: Relaxed, casual dining
text: The restaurant was a relaxed casual dining room with TV & pool table for entertainment. The meals and service was good.

title: Beautiful views at sunset.
text: The staff, drinks and food were all beautiful. Lovely lounges and seating areas to watch the sunset in the evenings. Staff made us very welcome. I was unable to book a floating pod as they were all reserved. But as we were one of the first to spend $1M rupee we received one of the sunken lounges.

title: Delayed flight
text: Our flight was delayed by 18 hours due to a engineering issue. We had 24 hours notice so had plenty of time to organise an extra nights accommodation. Reimbursed $150 for accommodation and $30 for meals. Meal voucher $10 provided at airport on deck-in to get breakfast. Plane clean and meals ok, except the egg omelette was overcooked. Had to go looking for staff to get a drink of water as call button was not working.

title: Great entertainment
text: The entertainment was the highlight, the dancing, music etc was very good. The food orders took a long time to be taken, we had to notify a waiter we were ready to order food even though drink orders had been taken twice. Food very disappointing.

title: Very affordable food
text: The food was very affordable and the service was quick. The food is nothing flash but great if you want a quick bit to eat, in a relaxed friendly location. The staff were great organizing a taxi at the end of the night.

title: Great food
text: The food was nicely cooked and everything was fresh. Unfortunately as we were there over Ramadan they were unable to get stock from their suppliers so not everything was on the menu. The steak was very good, The service was good and the staff were helpful getting us a taxi at the end of the night.

title: Great location to watch sunset
text: This was a great location to go to watch the sunset. Food and drinks on the expensive side of things. Take the stairs down, its quicker than waiting for the cable car. Plenty of table and chairs but get their early to get a great position. There are umbrellas available to shade yourself with as it can get very hot waiting for the sun to set. Staff were very friendly and helpful, even taking photos for us.

title: Traditional Mall
text: This is a tradition mall with normal shops and a section dedicated to tourist souveigners. There were very clean toilets available.

title: Very nice shopping centre
text: This is a new clean, modern shopping center with a variety of western shops, restaurants and a cinema. Also a good place to get out of the sun.

title: Open air shopping mall
text: This is an open air shopping mall with plenty of western and tourist shops, restuarants and a department store.

title: Beautiful pottery
text: This place had beautiful pottery and glassware at affordable prices. It was a great place to get great gifts for family and friends.

title: Popular beach
text: This was a very good sandy beach for families. The water was warm and clean but very crowded with tourists. it was patrolled by life guards. Lots of steps down and a bit of a squash going through the tunnel with people coming up.

title: Great place to watch the surfing
text: It was nice to sit back on the cliff tops watching the surfers going in and out. We had drinks and nibbles and it was very relaxing. Clean bar and toilets. The staff were very friendly

title: Nice temple & gardens
text: This temple and gardens was nice to walk around. There are steps so not suitable for wheel chairs. The views from the cliff tops are great. There was even a wedding when we were there. watch out for the monkeys stealing your sunglasses etc.

title: Lovely resturant and bakery
text: All the food was lovely and fresh, service was good and prices reasonable. Would recommend this as a nice place for lunch. Nice clean and quite.
